===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr}} {{term|dogmatique}}, from {{etyl|LL.}} {{term|dogmaticus}}, from Hellenistic {{etyl|grc}} {{term|δογματικός||didactic|lang=grc}}, from {{term|δόγμα||dogma|lang=grc}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/dɒɡˈmatɪk/}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# {{philosophy|medicine}} Adhering only to [[principle]]s which are true ''[[a priori]]'', rather than truths based on evidence or deduction.
# Pertaining to [[dogma]]s; [[doctrinal]].
# Asserting [[dogma]]s or [[belief]]s in a superior or arrogant way; [[opinionated]], [[dictatorial]].

